Turkey May Propose Edem Basci as New Bank Governor on Friday, Star Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-04-14T05:13:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/turkey-may-propose-edem-basci-as-new-bank-governor-tomorrow-star-reports.html
Turkey’s government may ask
President Abdullah Gul to approve Erdem Basci as the next
central bank governor tomorrow, Star newspaper reported, without
saying how it got the information.   The strongest candidate for the job is Deputy Governor
Erdem Basci, the newspaper said. The final decision rests with
Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan  and Deputy Prime Minister
 Ali Babacan , it said.  The government will ask the president in Ankara for
approval tomorrow in order to clear the way for an announcement
over the weekend and a handover on April 18, when Governor
Durmus Yilmaz’s term ends, the newspaper said.  It said Cabinet members had been asked to sign a blank
request for the president. The name will be filled in before the
document is submitted, Star said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
